profile.profileDescription: Use this profile if you want a system that is compliant with SPECTRUM: The UK Museum Documentation Standard

label.name: Description
label.description: Narrative description. This is the primary text used to document the item.

label.name: Source of description
label.description: Source of item description. This should be a formal citation if possible. For informal sources a narrative description is acceptable.

label.name: Caption
label.description: Short descriptive caption for item.

label.name: Caption
label.description: Short descriptive subtitle for item.

label.name: Georeference
label.description: Coordinates documenting the location of the item linking to GoogleMaps.

label.name: GeoNames
label.description: A Geographic lookup that takes search text, passes it to the GeoNames search service and provides a dropdown with search results (ordered by score). Selected geoname is stored as both text (name, country, continent and ID) and the service URL identifier.

label.name: Library of Congress Subject Headings
label.description: Library of Congress Subject headings describing this object. To add a new heading simply type the first few letters of the heading and choose the desired one from the displayed list of possible matches.

label.name: Notes (internal use only)
label.description: Notes regarding item

label.name: Object audit category
label.description: A code indicating the prioity of an object for auditing purposes.

label.name: Object audit date
label.description: The date an object was last checked in its location.

label.name: Object audit note
label.description: Additional information about the result or circumstances of the audit of an object.

label.name: Object audit result
label.description: The result of an audit of an object.

label.name: Object audit type
label.description: The type of audit carried out on an object.

label.name: Field collection date
label.description: The date an object is collected in the field.

label.name: Field collection event name
label.description: The name of the event at which an object was collected. Maintian a list of Standard terms.

label.name: Field collection event reference number
label.description: The unique number assigned to a field collection event. The number should also refer to a file containing written documentation about the event.

label.name: Field collection method
label.description: The method used to excavate or collect an object in the field. Maintain a standard list of terms.

label.name: Field collection note
label.description: Additional information about the place or method of field collection or excavation.

label.name: Field collection number
label.description: A number or code assigned to an object in the field before an Entry number or Object number is assigned.

label.name: Field collection place
label.description: The place where an object was excavated or collected in the field.

label.name: Field collection source
label.description: The social, socio-professional, or ethnic groups from which an object was collected or bought. May be different from the group of production and/or the group use.

label.name: Field collector
label.description: The person or organisation responsible for collecting a specimen or object in the field.

label.name: Geological complex name
label.description: The name of the geological complex from which a geological specimin was collected. Maintain a list of standard terms.

label.name: Habitat
label.description: A term describing the surroundings and environment of the area where a specimin was collected in the field.

label.name: Habitat note
label.description: Additional information about the habitiat of an object which has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Stratigraphic information
label.description: To be used to record statigraphic information. Refer to the SPECTRUM documentation for description of each element.

label.name: Completeness information
label.description: To be used to record completeness information of an object. Refer to the SPECTRUM documentation for description of each element.

label.name: Condition information
label.description: To be used to record condition information of an object. Refer to the SPECTRUM documentation for description of each element.

label.name: Conservation treatment policy
label.description: A term describing an object's need for Conservation treatment.

label.name: Environmental condition
label.description: A record of the environmental conditions in which an object kept.

label.name: Next condition check/assessment date
label.description: The date on which the next condition check or technical assessment is due.

label.name: Technical Assessment
label.description: Detailed assessment of the condition of an object and the required treatment.

label.name: Hazard information
label.description: To be used to record hazard information of an object. Refer to the SPECTRUM documentation for description of each element.

label.name: Conservation material
label.description: The materials used in the conservation of an object.

label.name: Conservation note
label.description: Additional information about the conservation of an object which has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Recall date
label.description: The date on which the next stage of the conservation process is due.

label.name: Treatment date
label.description: The date on which conservation treatment is completed.

label.name: Treatment report
label.description: Detailed description of the conservation treatment undergone by an object.

label.name: Age
label.description: The numeric age of a natural science specimin when it died. Use Age unit to describe the unit of measurement used and Age qualifier to qualify the information. Use Phase for a textual description of Age.

label.name: Age qualifier
label.description: A qualification of the statement of the Age of a natural science specimen.

label.name: Age unit
label.description: The unit of measurement used to describe the Age of a natural history specimin.

label.name: Colour
label.description: The colour of an object.

label.name: Content - activity
label.description: An activity depicted in or described by an object.

label.name: Content - concept
label.description: A concept depicted in or described by an object.

label.name: Content - date
label.description: A date depicted in or described by an object

label.name: Content - description
label.description: A general description of a depiction in an object, or description of an object without making interpretation. This may include descriptions of the content of all audio and visual works. (Use Brief description and Physical description to describe an object's other features.)

label.name: Content event
label.description: An event depicted in or described by an object.

label.name: Content - note
label.description: Additional information about an object's content which has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Content object
label.description: An object depicted in or described by another object.

label.name: Content other
label.description: An aspect of the content depicted in or described in an object

label.name: Content - position
label.description: The position on an object of a depiction or description.

label.name: Copy number
label.description: A number assigned to an object by the maker within a limited edition or special run.

label.name: Dimensions
label.description: Physical dimensions of object

label.name: Width
label.description: Width of object; enter in your preferred units (eg. 10cm

label.name: Height
label.description: Height of object; enter in your preferred units (eg. 10cm

label.name: Depth
label.description: Depth of object; enter in your preferred units (eg. 10cm

label.name: Circumference
label.description: circumference of object; enter in your preferred units (eg. 10cm

label.name: Edition number
label.description: A number assigned to a group of objects produced at the same time by the maker.

label.name: Form
label.description: The method used to mount or preserve a specimen.

label.name: Material information
label.description: The basic materials and media from which an object is constructed.

label.name: Object status
label.description: A statement of the standing of a natural science specimen or another object in relation to others in existence.

label.name: Phase
label.description: A textual expression of the age or developmental phase of a natural science specimen.

label.name: Physical description
label.description: General visual appearance of an object.

label.name: Sex
label.description: The gender of an animal specimen.

label.name: Style
label.description: Stypes or schools relating to an object.

label.name: Technical attribute
label.description: The name of a technical attribute possessed by an object which can be described and quantified.

label.name: Object component
label.description: The non-seperable part or component of an object which is being described.

label.name: Associated activity
label.description: An activity associated an object or group of objects

label.name: Associated concept
label.description: A concept associated with an object or group of objects.

label.name: Associated cultural affinity
label.description: A wider cultural context to which an object or group of objects relates.

label.name: Associated date
label.description: A date associated with an object or group of objects.

label.name: Associated note
label.description: A narrative description of the naure of the association of an organisation, poeple, person or place, with the object being recorded (e.g. design influences and design impact).

label.name: Object history note
label.description: The history of an object, including its creation, owners, vendors and the circumstances surrounding such events. Record information here which has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Ownership category
label.description: A term defining the type of ownership exisitng for an object before title was transferred to the organization.

label.name: Ownership dates
label.description: The dates when a People

label.name: Ownership exchange method
label.description: The means by which title to an object is transferred between two Owners, before title was tranferred to the organisation.

label.name: Ownership exchange note
label.description: Additional information about the ownership exchange, before title was transferred to the organisation, which has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Ownership exchange price
label.description: The total price paid for an object at when the title passed between two owners, including taxes for which the transfer is liable.

label.name: Usage
label.description: A single term describing the use of a particular kind of object.

label.name: Other number
label.description: An alternate numberfor an object other than the Object number.

label.name: Brief description
label.description: A text description of an object in approximately one sentence; normally used for administrative and identification purposes. It records the most important information from a number of seperate descriptive units of information.

label.name: Comments
label.description: Additional comments made about an object by visitors, curators or researchers.

label.name: Distinguishing features
label.description: A description of features which could uniquely identify an object, bringing together details from other groups of units of information such as Identification, Inscription, Condition which could in a sentence uniquely indentify an object.

label.name: Responsible Department
label.description: The responsible department. Omitted from published list, but referred to.

label.name: Owner's personal experience
label.description: A description of how and why a particular object or group of objects is known to have been of particular importance to a previous owner.

label.name: Owner's personal response
label.description: A description of the way in which a previous owner responded intuitively to the object.

label.name: Owner's reference
label.description: Documentation of any additional reference to the object provided by a previous owner, e.g. an event, object, document, person or organisation.

label.name: Owner's contribution note
label.description: Any observations or comments on a previous owner's contributions which the organisation whishs to record, e.g. the way in which th information was obtained or any discrepancies noted.

label.name: Object production date
label.description: The date when a stage in the design, creation or manufacture of an object took place.

label.name: Object production note
label.description: Additional information about an object's production.

label.name: Object production reason
label.description: The reason why an object was produced.

label.name: Technique
label.description: Processes

label.name: Display recommendations
label.description: Specific recommendations for the display of an object in addition to the measures which would normally be taken for that type of object.

label.name: Environmental recommendations
label.description: Specific recommendations for the environment in which an object is to be displayed or stored in addition to the measures which would normally be taken for that type of object.

label.name: Packing recommendations
label.description: Specific recommendations for packing an object in addition to the measures which would normally be taken for that type of object.

label.name: Security recommendations
label.description: Specific recommendations for the security of an object in addition to the measures which would normally be taken for that type of object.

label.name: Special requirements
label.description: Requirements that may be unique or special to a particular object.

label.name: Storage requirements
label.description: Specific recommendations for the storage of an object in addition to the measures which would normally be taken for that type of object.

label.name: Salvage priority
label.description: A record of the salvage priority assigned to an object or group of objects.

label.name: Legal/licence requirements
label.description: Details of any legislation (other than associated rights) which applies to an object while in the organisation's custody, whether acquired or not.

label.name: Legal/licence requirements held
label.description: Details of any licences or certificates held (other than copyright or other rights of use or performance) which applies to an object while in the organisation's custody, whether acquired or not.

label.name: Right begin date
label.description: The first date on which a right is current.

label.name: Right end date
label.description: The last date on which a right is current.

label.name: Right note
label.description: Any details of the rights not covered elsewhere.

label.name: Right reference number
label.description: A unique number identifying a right.

label.name: Right type
label.description: The specific type of right being recorded in relation to an object, document, photograph, work of art or record.

label.name: Access category
label.description: A record of the level of access allowed to an object or group of objects based on their needs or significance.

label.name: Credit line
label.description: Text acknowledging a donation or loan

label.name: Label information
label.description: The text used for an exhibition or display label or a handlist or catalogue.

label.name: Object display status
label.description: The stage in the Use of collections procedure which an individual object to be displayed, has reached.

label.name: Object valuation
label.description: The current worth of an object as assigned by a Valuer.

label.name: Object valuation date
label.description: The date the valuation of an object is assigned.

label.name: Object valuation note
label.description: Additional information about the valuation of an object or group of objects.

label.name: Object valuation renewal
label.description: The date the valuation of an object is assigned.

label.name: Authorisation date
label.description: The date on which an authoriser gives final approval for a procedure to take place.

label.name: Cost
label.description: The amount paid in the course of a procedure.

label.name: Procedure dates
label.description: The dates on which a procedure is begun and ended.

label.name: Procedure Note
label.description: Additional information about procedure which has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Procedure title
label.description: The name assigned to a procedure or project carried.

label.name: Reason
label.description: The reason for the procedure taking place.

label.name: Request
label.description: Details provided by the person or organisation making a request for a procedure or process to occur.

label.name: Requested action date
label.description: The date on which a requester wishes for a procedure to occur.

label.name: Scheduled begin date
label.description: The date on which a procedure is scheduled to begin.

label.name: Scheduled end date
label.description: The date on which a procedure is scheduled to end.

label.name: Status
label.description: The stage in the procedure which an individual object has reached.

label.name: Accession date
label.description: The date on which an object formally enters the collections and is recorded in the accessions register.

label.name: Acquisition authorisation
label.description: The name of a member of staff giving final approval for the acquisition to proceed. The date on which the Acquisition authoriser gives final approval for an acquisition to proceed.

label.name: Acquisition date
label.description: The date on which title to an object or group of objects is transferred to the organisation.

label.name: Aquisition Funding Info
label.description: The funding used to support the acquisition of an object.

label.name: Acquisition method
label.description: The means by which title to an object is formally transferred to the organisation.

label.name: Acquisition note
label.description: General information about the acquisition.

label.name: Acquisition provisos
label.description: Restrictions applying to the objects in a single acquisition

label.name: Acquisition reason
label.description: The reason or justification for an acquisition.

label.name: Acquisition reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for information on the acquisition of an object or group of objects. It should serve as the reference to written documentation of a valuation. This will normally be the object number.

label.name: Acquisition source
label.description: The People

label.name: Group purchase price
label.description: The total price paid for a group of objects at acquisition

label.name: Object offer price
label.description: The price at which an object is offered for sale to the organisation.

label.name: Object purchaser offer price
label.description: The price which the organisation offers for the purchase of an object.

label.name: Object purchase price
label.description: The total price paid for an object at acquisition

label.name: Original object purchase price
label.description: The price paid for an object in the original currency at the time of purchase.

label.name: Transfer of title number
label.description: A unique identifying number for a transfer of title or acquisition event. It should serveas the reference to written documentation of a transfer of title or acquisition process.The number may be assigned to a transfer of title form.

label.name: Audit method
label.description: The method used to audit an object or group of objects.

label.name: Audit reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for the audit of an object or group of objects. It shouldserve as the reference to written documentation of an audit.

label.name: Audit type
label.description: The type of audit carried out on a object

label.name: Condition check/assessment date
label.description: The date(s) on which a condition check or technical assessment process took place.

label.name: Condition check/assessment method
label.description: The method used when carrying out a condition check or technical assessment process.

label.name: Condition check/assessment note
label.description: Additional information about the condition checking or technical assessment processwhich has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Condition check/assessment reason
label.description: The reason for a condition check or technical assessment process taking place.

label.name: Condition check/assessment reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for the condition checking or technical assessmentprocess. It should serve as the reference to written documentation of a conditioncheck or technical assessment.

label.name: Conservation method
label.description: The method used in the conservation of an object.

label.name: Conservation Reference Number
label.description: A unique identifying number for the conservation of an object or group of objects. Itshould serve as the reference to written documentation of conservation.

label.name: Deaccession date
label.description: The date when an item was struck off the accession register.

label.name: Disposal date
label.description: The date an object is disposed of.

label.name: Disposal method
label.description: The way in which an object is disposed of.

label.name: Disposal new object number
label.description: The object number assigned to a deaccessioned object by the recipient.

label.name: Disposal note
label.description: Additional information about the disposal of an object which has not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Disposal price
label.description: The total price paid for an object at disposal

label.name: Disposal provisos
label.description: Restrictions applying to all the objects to be disposed of.

label.name: Disposal reason
label.description: The reason or justification for an object or objects being disposed of.

label.name: Disposal Reference number
label.description: The unique number assigned to the disposal of an object or group of objects. Thenumber should also refer to a file containing all written documentation about thedisposal.

label.name: Group disposal price
label.description: The total price paid for a group of objects at disposal including taxes for which thepurchase is liable. If individual prices are known for specific objects in the group

label.name: Indemnity confirmation date
label.description: The date confirmation of indemnity cover is received from the indemnifying body.

label.name: Indemnity note
label.description: Additional information about the indemnity

label.name: Indemnity renewal date
label.description: The date when a Government Indemnity arrangement is due for renewal.

label.name: Indemnity Reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number of the indemnity as assigned by the organisation. Thenumber should be a reference to written documentation about the indemnity

label.name: Object minimum liability sum
label.description: The sum determined by Government Indemnity Scheme which the indemnified organisation is responsible.

label.name: Insurance note
label.description: Additional information about the insurance

label.name: Insurance policy number
label.description: The number of the insurance policy as assigned by the Insurer.

label.name: Insurance reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number of the insurance as assigned by the organisation. Thenumber should be a reference to written documentation about the indemnity

label.name: Insurance renewal date
label.description: The date when an insurance policy is due for renewal.

label.name: Lender's authorisation date
label.description: The date on which the lender's authoriser gives approval for a loan in to proceed.

label.name: Loan in conditions
label.description: Conditions applying to objects as part of the loan in agreement

label.name: Loan in note
label.description: General information about a loan in.

label.name: Loan in reference number
label.description: The unique number assigned to the loan of objects from outside the organisation.The number should also refer to a file containing written documentation about theloan.

label.name: Loan out note
label.description: General information about a loan out.

label.name: Loan out reference number
label.description: The unique number assigned to the loan of objects to other organisations. Thenumber should also refer to a file containing all written documentation about the loanout.

label.name: Loaned object status
label.description: The stage in the Loans out procedure which an individual object to be loaned out has reached.

label.name: Special conditions of loan
label.description: A statement of conditions on the loan of an object from an organisation in addition to those normally laid down.

label.name: Loss/damage date
label.description: The date an object was first established as damaged or missing.

label.name: Loss/damage method
label.description: The method by which an object or group of objects was lost to the collections.

label.name: Loss/damage note
label.description: Additional information about the loss of an object

label.name: Loss/damage reference number
label.description: The unique number assigned to the record of the loss of an object or group of objects.The number should also refer to a file containing all written documentation about theloss of an object.

label.name: Movement method
label.description: The method used in the movement of an object.

label.name: Movement note
label.description: Additional information about the movement of an object or group of objects whichhas not been recorded elsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Movement reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for the movement of an object or group of objects. Itshould serve as the reference to written documentation of a movement.

label.name: Planned removal date
label.description: The date an object is due to be returned from a Current location which is not its Normal location.

label.name: Removal date
label.description: The date an object is actually removed from a Current location.

label.name: Depositor's requirements
label.description: Requirements made by a depositor or owner concerning the deposit of an object orgroup of objects

label.name: Entry date
label.description: The date on which an object or group of objects enters the organisation.

label.name: Entry method
label.description: The method by which an object or group of objects is deposited.

label.name: Entry note
label.description: Additional information about the deposit of an object which has not been recordedelsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Entry number
label.description: A unique number assigned to the entry of an object or group of objects and used totrack objects prior to their return or acquisition. It should serve as the reference towritten documentation of objects entering the organisation for the first time. Thenumber should be the one assigned to an entry form or receipt.

label.name: Entry reason
label.description: The reason for an object or group of objects physically entering the organisation.

label.name: Packing note
label.description: Information about the packing of an object or group of objects at the time of deposit at the organisation.

label.name: Return date
label.description: The date an object is due to be returned to or collected by the Current owner or Depositor.

label.name: Delivery date
label.description: The precise date on which an object or objects leaving the organisation is due to bedelivered at its destination.

label.name: Exit date
label.description: The date on which an object or objects leaves the organisation.

label.name: Exit method
label.description: The method by which an object or group of objects leaves the organisation.

label.name: Exit note
label.description: Additional information relating to the exit of an object which cannot be recorded elsewhere.

label.name: Exit reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for a exit. It should serve as the reference to writtendocumentation of a exit. The number may be assigned to a exit note or receipt.

label.name: Shipping note
label.description: Additional information about shipping an object

label.name: Process Date
label.description: The date on which a process is completed.

label.name: Process method
label.description: The method used to carry out the process on an object.

label.name: Process note
label.description: Additional information about the process of an object which has not been recordedelsewhere using controlled terminology.

label.name: Process reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for the process carried out on an object or group ofobjects. It should serve as the reference to written documentation of a process.

label.name: Valuation reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for the valuation of an object or group of objects. Itshould serve as the reference to written documentation of a valuation.

label.name: Exhibition reference number
label.description: A unique identifying number for the exhibition of an object or group of objects underthe auspices of the organisation. It should serve as the reference to writtendocumentation of an exhibition.

label.name: Exhibition begin date
label.description: The opening date of an exhibition

label.name: Exhibition end date
label.description: The closing date of an exhibition

label.name: Exhibition title
label.description: The name of an exhibition

label.name: Venue
label.description: The Organisation responsible for the venue where an exhibition is to be held.

label.name: Research/use of object date
label.description: The date an object is researched

label.name: Research/use of object method
label.description: The way in which an object is researched

label.name: Research/use of object note
label.description: Additional information about the research or use of an object which has not beenrecorded elsewhere using controlled terminology. This could include an object'soperations log.

label.name: Research/use of object provisos
label.description: Restrictions applying to the research or use of an object.

label.name: Research/use of object reference number
label.description: The unique number assigned to the research or use of an object or group of objects.The number should also refer to a file containing all written documentation about thedisposal.

label.name: Research/use of object result
label.description: Information about the outcome of the research or use of object(s).

label.name: Researcher/user
label.description: The Person or Organisation researching

label.name: Date association
label.description: How a Date relates to an event in an object's history.

label.name: Earliest Date
label.description: The earliest probable or exact date at which an event in an object's history is thought to have occurred.

label.name: latest Date
label.description: The latest probable date at which an event in an object's history is thought to have occurred.

label.name: Date period
label.description: A textual expression of the period when an event in an object's history is thought to have occurred. Use a single term. Maintain a list of standard terms

label.name: Date text
label.description: The textual expression of the date or date span when an event in an object's history is thought to have occurred.

label.name: Location Access note
label.description: Information about the access to a specific Location.

label.name: Location condition
label.description: Information about the condition of the location

label.name: Location security note
label.description: Information about the security of a specific Location

label.name: Location security note
label.description: The nature or category of a Location.

label.name: Contact name
label.description: The representative of an Organisation who is normally liaised with.

label.name: Organisation dissolution date
label.description: The date on which an Organisation formally ceased to be. This may be the date onwhich it was taken over or wound up.

label.name: Organisation foundation date
label.description: The date on which an Organisation formally came into being.

label.name: Organisation foundation place
label.description: Information about the place where an Organisation came into being.

label.name: Organisation function
label.description: The activities which make up the main business of an organisation.

label.name: Organisation group
label.description: The social

label.name: Organisation history
label.description: Information about the history of the Organisation.

label.name: Organisation history
label.description: The Collections Trust assigned code uniquely identifying an Organisation.

label.name: Organisation main body
label.description: The name of an Organisation.

label.name: Organisation sub-body
label.description: The name of the sub-body of an Organisation.

label.name: People's culture
label.description: An identifiable type of civilisation.

label.name: People's group
label.description: An identifiable community or division of a nation of People.

label.name: People's linguistic group
label.description: A broad grouping of People identifiable by common linguistic roots.

label.name: Person biographical note
label.description: Information about the personal history of a Person.

label.name: Vital Dates
label.description: Enter the birth and death dates for an entity.

label.name: Person's gender
label.description: Information about the personal history of a Person.

label.name: Person's nationality
label.description: A Person's official current nationality.

label.name: Person's occupation
label.description: The occupation or employment of a Person.

label.name: Person's salutation
label.description: The form of greeting used in correspondence.

label.name: Person's school/style
label.description: The form of greeting used in correspondence.

label.name: Place context
label.description: A number

label.name: Place environmental details
label.description: Environmental information relevant to an object

label.name: Place feature
label.description: The name by which a feature associated with an object is normally known.

label.name: Place name type
label.description: The nature or category of Place recorded.

label.name: Place note
label.description: Additional information about Place which has not been recorded elsewhere usingcontrolled terminology.

label.name: Place position
label.description: A precise position in a Place

label.name: Place reference number type
label.description: The category of Place reference number recorded.

label.name: Place status
label.description: A formal administrative or scientific status assigned to a place.

label.name: Place type system
label.description: The classification system from which the Place feature type is taken.

label.name: Confidentiality note
label.description: Restrictions agreed on the publication of details of an object

label.name: Information usage
label.description: Information on the use made of the record and associated resources

label.name: Record type
label.description: Describes the level of description which the record contains.

label.name: Reference details
label.description: Details

label.name: Reference Note
label.description: Details of the specific nature of the relevance of the Reference to the object

label.name: Reference publication date
